# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Verified and completed the Vercel Web Analytics installation for this Next.js App Router project.

## Findings
The project **already had Vercel Web Analytics properly configured**:
- `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already declared in `package.json`
- The `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/next` was already imported in `src/app/layout.tsx`
- The `<Analytics />` component was already properly placed within the `<body>` tag in the root layout

## Actions Taken
1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart to ensure compliance with current best practices
2. **Verified Framework Configuration**: Confirmed the implementation follows the correct Next.js App Router pattern (Analytics component in root layout)
3. **Installed Dependencies**: Ran `npm install` to ensure all packages including `@vercel/analytics@2.0.1` are properly installed
4. **Build Verification**: Successfully ran `npm run build` - build completed without errors
5. **Linting**: Ran `npm run lint` - no linting errors detected
6. **Tests**: No test suite is configured in this project (no test scripts in package.json)

## Files Modified
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with installed dependencies

## Implementation Details
The project uses the official Vercel Analytics setup for Next.js App Router:
```typescript
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';

// In root layout component:
<body>
  <WalletProvider>
    {children}
  </WalletProvider>
  <Analytics />
</body>
```

This implementation follows the exact pattern specified in the Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects.

## Next Steps for Project Owner
1. Ensure Analytics is enabled in the Vercel project dashboard
2. Deploy the application to Vercel to activate tracking
3. Verify data collection by checking browser Network tab for `/_vercel/insights/view` requests after deployment
4. Monitor the analytics dashboard in Vercel after users visit the site

## Verification Results
✅ Package installed: `@vercel/analytics@2.0.1`
✅ Build successful: Next.js production build completed
✅ Linting passed: No errors or warnings
